<subSubSection id="C368652E935C8E01F2AAFA85FC6CFAB2" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935C8E01F2AAFA85FC6CFAB2" blockId="5.[151,1437,1303,1977]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">
<materialsCitation id="3B1A3CF8935C8E01F2AAFA85FC6CFAB2" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798147309" collectionCode="R" collectorName="P. Pantel " pageId="5" pageNumber="489" specimenCount="3" typeStatus="lectotype">
<typeStatus id="54C98807935C8E01F2AAFA85FED6FAFA" box="[151,263,1303,1329]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">Lectotype</typeStatus>
(present designation: beetle labelled but not published by Pantel and Mlynář) is a male bearing labels “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F299FAA9FEF5FA9F" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[164,292,1339,1364]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="contemptus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F299FAA9FEF5FA9F" box="[164,292,1339,1364]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">contemptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
m. in Hispania”, “ex-Museo Chaudoir”, “ 
<collectionCode id="ED63AE60935C8E01F13CFAA9FCC9FA9E" box="[769,792,1339,1365]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">R</collectionCode>
. 
<collectorName id="26875373935C8E01F119FAA9FC5AFA9E" box="[804,907,1339,1365]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">P. Pantel</collectorName>
”, “ 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935C8E01F196FAA9FB96FA9E" box="[939,1095,1339,1365]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">HOLOTYPE</typeStatus>
”, “vidit 1974 
<collectorName id="26875373935C8E01F6D8FAA9FA8FFA9E" box="[1253,1374,1339,1365]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">Z. Mylnář</collectorName>
”, and “ 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935C8E01F29CFACDFEC5FAB2" box="[161,276,1375,1401]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">Lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F304FACDFD14FAB2" authority="Dejean, 1829" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[313,709,1375,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="contemptus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F304FACDFDFBFAB3" box="[313,554,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">Harpalus contemptus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935C8E01F00DFACDFD14FAB2" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[560,709,1375,1401]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
desig. by 
<collectorName id="26875373935C8E01F104FACDFC7FFAB2" box="[825,942,1375,1401]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">J. Serrano</collectorName>
”.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368652E935C8E01F2FAFA11FCB4F872" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935C8E01F2FAFA11FB91FA0A" blockId="5.[151,1437,1303,1977]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">
<materialsCitation id="3B1A3CF8935C8E01F2FAFA11FBECFA0A" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798147312" country="Spain" location="Possibly" municipality="Mlynar" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935C8E01F2FAFA11FEB8FA56" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[199,361,1411,1437]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean (1829)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that he studied two individuals collected in 
<collectingCountry id="F3657635935C8E01F1E6FA11FBCAFA56" box="[987,1051,1411,1437]" name="Spain" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">Spain</collectingCountry>
. 
<location id="8EAD607E935C8E01F617FA11FB5BFA56" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03DB87B3935C8E01F2AAFB5CFCB4F872:8EAD607E935C8E01F617FA11FB5BFA56" box="[1066,1162,1411,1437]" country="Spain" municipality="Mlynar" name="Possibly" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">Possibly</location>
, 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BA9ACDF935C8E01F6ABFA11FB39FA56" box="[1174,1256,1411,1437]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">Mlynář</collectingMunicipality>
only received a single beetle for study and this is why he labelled it with a red card “ 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935C8E01F1A8FA35FBE3FA0A" box="[917,1074,1447,1473]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">HOLOTYPE</typeStatus>
”
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935C8E01F2FAFA59FCB4F872" blockId="5.[151,1437,1303,1977]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">
The species is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F039FA59FC8AFA2E" authority="Reitter, 1900" authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1900" box="[516,859,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuelimbatus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F039FA59FD13FA2E" box="[516,706,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">H. tenuelimbatus</emphasis>
Reitter, 1900
</taxonomicName>
, whose 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935C8E01F18FFA59FBC5FA2E" box="[946,1044,1483,1509]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">syntypes</typeStatus>
were designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935C8E01F6C8FA59FA49FA2E" author="Kataev, B. M." box="[1269,1432,1483,1509]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" pagination="188 - 278" refId="ref11264" refString="Kataev, B. M. (1989) New data on the ground-beetles of the genera Pangus and Harpalus (Coleoptera, Carabidae) with a revision of some Palaeartic species groups Nasekomye Mongolii. Vol. 10. Nauka, Leningrad, 188 - 278. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1989">Kataev (1989)</bibRefCitation>
. Kataev corrected the statement of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935C8E01F02BFA7DFD67F9C2" author="Jeanne, C." box="[534,694,1519,1545]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" pagination="87 - 96" refId="ref11165" refString="Jeanne, C. (1971) Carabiques de la Peninsule Iberique (11 eme note). Bulletin de la Societe Linneenne de Bordeaux, 1 (4), 87 - 96." type="journal article" year="1971">Jeanne (1971)</bibRefCitation>
, who considered 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F144FA7DFBE9F9C2" authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1900" box="[889,1080,1519,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuelimbatus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F144FA7DFBE9F9C2" box="[889,1080,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">H. tenuelimbatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F6C1FA7DFE76F9E6" authority="(Duftschmid, 1812)" baseAuthorityName="Duftschmid" baseAuthorityYear="1812" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distinguendus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F6C1FA7DFF6FF9E6" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">H. distinguendus</emphasis>
(Duftschmid, 1812)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F38FF981FD84F9E7" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[434,597,1555,1580]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="contemptus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F38FF981FD84F9E7" box="[434,597,1555,1580]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">H. contemptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F102F981FB9DF9E6" authority="Dejean, 1829" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[831,1100,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblitus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F102F981FC7FF9E6" box="[831,942,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">H. oblitus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935C8E01F18BF981FB9DF9E6" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[950,1100,1555,1581]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and is endemic to the Iberian Peninsula; this may explain the lack of works describing its characteristics except for the review of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935C8E01F6C9F9A5FA46F99A" author="Kataev, B. M." box="[1268,1431,1591,1617]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" pagination="188 - 278" refId="ref11264" refString="Kataev, B. M. (1989) New data on the ground-beetles of the genera Pangus and Harpalus (Coleoptera, Carabidae) with a revision of some Palaeartic species groups Nasekomye Mongolii. Vol. 10. Nauka, Leningrad, 188 - 278. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="1989">Kataev (1989)</bibRefCitation>
, who also illustrated the aedeagus. In the key of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935C8E01F094F9C9FC97F9BE" author="Fuente de la, J. M." box="[681,838,1627,1653]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" refId="ref10490" refString="Fuente de la, J. M. (1927) Tablas analiticas para la clasificacion de los coleopteros de la Peninsula Iberica. Adephaga: I Cicindelidae, II Carabidae. J. Bosch, Barcelona, 415 pp." type="book" year="1927">Fuente (1927)</bibRefCitation>
the species appears as an aberration of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F6C3F9C9FEDEF952" authority="Dejean, 1829" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblitus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F6C3F9C9FABAF9BE" box="[1278,1387,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">H. oblitus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935C8E01F74FF9C9FEDEF952" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." pageId="5" pageNumber="489" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, mixed with other aberrations not easy to be separated. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935C8E01F147F9EDFBCCF952" author="Mlynar, Z." box="[890,1053,1663,1689]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" pagination="73 - 111" refId="ref11903" refString="Mlynar, Z. (1979) Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Osteuropaischen und Sibirischen Harpalus-Arten (Col., Carabidae). Koleopterologische Rundschau, 54, 73 - 111." type="journal article" year="1979">Mlynář (1979)</bibRefCitation>
did not refer to it when commenting on the synonyms of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F39AF931FDC4F976" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[423,533,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblitus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F39AF931FDC4F976" box="[423,533,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">H. oblitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Other available key to separate 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F1BAF931FBF8F977" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[903,1065,1699,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="contemptus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F1BAF931FBF8F977" box="[903,1065,1699,1724]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">H. contemptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F65DF931FAEBF976" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[1120,1338,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="oblitus" subSpecies="patruelis">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F65DF931FAEBF976" box="[1120,1338,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">H. oblitus patruelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935C8E01F289F955FE4DF92A" author="Novoa Docet, F." box="[180,412,1734,1761]" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" refId="ref12045" refString="Novoa Docet, F. (2015) Carabidae de la Sierra de Guadarrama. Tesis Doctoral, 1974. Publicaciones de la Universidad Complutense de Madrid, Madrid, 440 pp. [https: // eprints. ucm. es / 52116 / 1 / 5306703652. pdf]" type="book" year="2015">Novoa Docet (2015)</bibRefCitation>
. Comparison between 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F0A6F955FCECF92B" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[667,829,1735,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="contemptus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F0A6F955FCECF92B" box="[667,829,1735,1760]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">H. contemptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F14FF955FB9AF92A" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[882,1099,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="oblitus" subSpecies="patruelis">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F14FF955FB9AF92A" box="[882,1099,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">H. oblitus patruelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(the subspecies inhabiting the Iberian Peninsula) shows that 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F3D0F979FD41F8CF" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[493,656,1771,1796]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="contemptus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F3D0F979FD41F8CF" box="[493,656,1771,1796]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">H. contemptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a very fine and shallow microsculpture in the elytra that is more marked and visible in 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F3AEF89DFDBFF8E2" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[403,622,1807,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="oblitus" subSpecies="patruelis">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F3AEF89DFDBFF8E2" box="[403,622,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">H. oblitus patruelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the pronotum side of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F14DF89DFBC2F8E3" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[880,1043,1807,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="contemptus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F14DF89DFBC2F8E3" box="[880,1043,1807,1832]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">H. contemptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is almost straight toward posterior angle and not arcuate, the posterior angle of pronotum is well-marked and not rounded; the pronotum basis is somewhat arcuate whereas is straight in 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F026F8C5FD59F8BA" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[539,648,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblitus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F026F8C5FD59F8BA" box="[539,648,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">H. oblitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the aedeagus is much more robust in 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F612F8C5FB01F8BB" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[1071,1232,1879,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="contemptus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F612F8C5FB01F8BB" box="[1071,1232,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">H. contemptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the endophallus shows basally two small teeth not seen in 
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935C8E01F0AEF8E9FCA2F85E" box="[659,883,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935C8E01F0AEF8E9FCBFF85E" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[659,878,1915,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="489" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="oblitus" subSpecies="patruelis">H. oblitus patruelis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
As indicated above, the species is orophilous and endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="F3657635935C8E01F327F80DFEB1F872" box="[282,352,1951,1977]" name="Georgia" pageId="5" pageNumber="489">Iberia</collectingCountry>
: North and Central mountains, Sierra Nevada.
</paragraph>
